Police are hunting armed robbers who targeted a North Lanarkshire store. Armed robbers target Airdrie supermarket Police are hunting armed robbers who targeted a North Lanarkshire store.It is understood the men threatened a shop assistant with a knife and firearm before demanding cash at Tesco Express, in Airdrie High Street.The robbery happened yesterday at around 11.20pm.It is not known if they made off with any money. 